---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="The Future of Workforce" description="Explore how AI is reshaping real estate roles and the skills needed to thrive.">
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="py-20 px-6 bg-gradient-to-b from-primary/10 to-dark">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h1 class="text-5xl font-bold mb-6 text-primary">
        The Future of the Workforce
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-300 mb-8">
        Artificial Intelligence isn't replacing real estate professionals—it's elevating them. Discover how brokers, asset managers, analysts, and leaders are evolving in an AI-integrated market.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Content Sections -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6 max-w-4xl mx-auto">
    <!-- Key Statistics -->
    <div class="mb-12 p-8 rounded-lg bg-primary/5 border border-primary/20">
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-300 mb-2">
        <strong>37% of CRE tasks</strong> can be automated
      </p>
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-300 mb-2">
        <strong>92% of CRE companies</strong> have initiated AI pilots
      </p>
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-300">
        <strong>87% of brokerages</strong> actively use AI tools daily (2026)
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- The Shift -->
    <div class="space-y-12">
      <div class="border-l-4 border-primary pl-8">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4 gradient-text">
          How Specific Roles Are Evolving
        </h2>

        <div class="space-y-8 mt-6">
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-primary mb-2">Brokers & Leasing Agents</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-400 mb-3">
              AI is automating lead qualification, proposal drafting, and listing management. Brokers are redirecting time from administrative tasks to relationship building, complex negotiations, and strategic deal structuring. Teams using AI can effectively manage 200+ prospects instead of 100-150.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-primary mb-2">Asset Managers</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-400 mb-3">
              AI extracts lease terms in minutes (not hours), automates portfolio analysis across 17+ functional areas, and enables continuous performance optimization. Asset managers are shifting 100+ hours annually toward strategic capital allocation and repositioning.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-primary mb-2">Appraisers</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-400 mb-3">
              AI-powered valuation models achieve error rates below 3%, reducing manual preparation time by 50-70%. HelloData.ai generates rent comparables in under one minute (80% faster than traditional methods). Appraisers shift toward on-site inspections and judgment-based analysis.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-primary mb-2">Underwriters</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-400 mb-3">
              AI validates data instantly, flags anomalies in real-time, and processes loan files 50% faster. For multifamily properties, AI achieves 9/10 accuracy. Underwriters evolve toward risk assessment, deal structuring, and exception handling.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-primary mb-2">Market Analysts</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-400 mb-3">
              Real-time market analysis platforms reduce research time by 98%. Automated financial modeling enables instant scenario analysis. Analysts focus on competitive intelligence, trend interpretation, and investment thesis development.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-secondary pl-8">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4 gradient-text">
          Five Critical New Skills for Success
        </h2>

        <div class="space-y-6 mt-6">
          <div class="p-4 rounded bg-secondary/5">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-secondary mb-2">1. AI Literacy & Tool Fluency</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-400">Understanding what AI can and cannot do, knowing how to prompt systems effectively, and maintaining healthy skepticism about outputs. This is different from learning spreadsheets—it requires understanding AI's strengths and limitations.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="p-4 rounded bg-secondary/5">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-secondary mb-2">2. Data Interpretation & Judgment</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-400">The ability to interpret AI outputs, identify when results don't make intuitive sense, and exercise judgment about when to accept or challenge algorithmic recommendations becomes increasingly valuable.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="p-4 rounded bg-secondary/5">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-secondary mb-2">3. Strategic Relationship Management</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-400">As administrative tasks diminish, deeper relationship building, complex negotiation, and strategic partnership development become primary value drivers. This is fundamentally human work that AI cannot replicate.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="p-4 rounded bg-secondary/5">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-secondary mb-2">4. Market Domain Expertise</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-400">Deep knowledge of specific markets, property types, tenant behaviors, and economic cycles. AI excels at pattern recognition across large datasets, but understanding micro-market dynamics requires human expertise built over time.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="p-4 rounded bg-secondary/5">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-secondary mb-2">5. Ethical & Compliance Judgment</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-400">Understanding regulatory, ethical, and reputational implications of AI decisions. Professionals who understand fair lending laws, anti-discrimination requirements, and ethical practices are essential safeguards against algorithmic bias.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-accent pl-8">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4 gradient-text">
          The Augmented Professional in Action
        </h2>

        <div class="space-y-6 mt-6">
          <div>
            <h4 class="text-lg font-bold text-accent mb-2">The Accelerated Underwriting Process</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-400">A complex multifamily underwriting that historically took 2-3 weeks now takes 5-7 days with AI assistance. AI handles data validation and anomaly detection (2-3 hours), while underwriters redirect 40+ hours toward deal structuring, risk assessment, and strategic analysis—higher-value work that delivers better decisions.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h4 class="text-lg font-bold text-accent mb-2">The Expanded Broker Territory</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-400">A broker typically manages 100-150 active prospects. With AI-powered lead management, AI qualifies inbound leads and creates prioritized lists, generates personalized proposals, and tracks engagement. The broker redirects time from qualification to relationship building and complex negotiation, effectively managing 200+ prospects while spending more time on high-value activities.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h4 class="text-lg font-bold text-accent mb-2">The Market-Responsive Asset Manager</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-400">An asset manager managing 15-20 properties historically spent 40% of time on rent surveys and comparable analysis. With AI: rent surveys complete in minutes, comparable analysis updates continuously, financial reporting generates automatically with AI-driven variance analysis. The asset manager redirects 100+ hours annually toward repositioning strategy and capital allocation.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Economic Impact -->
    <div class="mt-12 p-8 rounded-lg bg-gradient-to-r from-primary/10 to-secondary/10 border border-primary/20">
      <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6">Economic Impact & Industry Transformation</h3>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-bold text-primary mb-2">Industry-Wide Impact</h4>
          <ul class="text-gray-400 space-y-2">
            <li>• $34B in efficiency gains expected over 5 years</li>
            <li>• 37% of CRE tasks can be automated</li>
            <li>• 63% of firms increasing AI budgets 5-25%</li>
            <li>• 25% planning increases exceeding 25%</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-bold text-secondary mb-2">The Reality Check</h4>
          <ul class="text-gray-400 space-y-2">
            <li>• Entry-level positions face most pressure</li>
            <li>• Office/admin support most automated</li>
            <li>• Unemployment concerns impact deal flow</li>
            <li>• But: net job creation expected long-term</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Reskilling -->
    <div class="mt-12 p-8 rounded-lg bg-accent/5 border border-accent/20">
      <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-accent">Training & Reskilling for the AI Era</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-400 mb-6">The industry has recognized the urgency of AI training. Over 700 CRE professionals have already participated in AI training programs. Effective training includes:</p>
      <ul class="text-gray-400 space-y-2">
        <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-accent">✓</span> <span>Hands-on tool training (IntellCRE, HelloData.ai, valuation platforms)</span></li>
        <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-accent">✓</span> <span>Prompt engineering for CRE-specific use cases</span></li>
        <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-accent">✓</span> <span>Data interpretation and critical judgment frameworks</span></li>
        <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-accent">✓</span> <span>Ethical and regulatory considerations</span></li>
        <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-accent">✓</span> <span>Integration with existing workflows and systems</span></li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 p-8 rounded-lg bg-gradient-to-r from-primary/20 to-secondary/20 border border-primary/20">
      <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">The Bottom Line</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">
        Commercial real estate is experiencing workforce <strong>evolution, not elimination</strong>. AI is not replacing brokers, appraisers, underwriters, or asset managers—it is eliminating the routine work they do and elevating their role to more strategic, relationship-driven, and judgment-based activities.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-300">
        The question for CRE professionals is not whether AI will impact your career. The question is whether you will lead that transformation or follow it. First movers who invest in AI training, maintain human judgment at critical decision points, and evolve their roles toward higher-value work will outcompete those who react slowly.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Navigation -->
  <section class="py-12 px-6 border-t border-primary/20">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto flex justify-between">
      <a href="/CREFuture/" class="text-gray-400 hover:text-primary transition">← Back Home</a>
      <a href="/CREFuture/transformation/" class="text-gray-400 hover:text-primary transition">Next: Transformation →</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
